This paper discusses the development and optimization of Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) in neuromorphic computing architectures. The focus is on reducing the size of the network while increasing its resilience to hardware faults. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely categories include cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
